chunk_content: The DQA requires 6 steps: 1) Setting up a country-based implementation team of stakeholders to agree on the scope and methods and to support the implementation and dissemination of the results of the DQA; 2) To agree on the sampling required and the indicators to include in the assessment and to finalize the site-level instruments; 3) Assessing at the site level to collect data, including assessing the HIV patient monitoring system and recreating the numbers of people receiving and initiating ART; 4) Conducting a desk review to identify challenges in national reporting (can take place simultaneously with step 3; 5) Analyzing the results and resetting the site-level and national numbers of people receiving and initiating ART; and 6) Developing a communication strategy and disseminating the updated values.
